.TH "snd_soc_dapm_ignore_suspend" 9 "snd_soc_dapm_ignore_suspend" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_soc_dapm_ignore_suspend \- ignore suspend status for DAPM endpoint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" snd_soc_dapm_ignore_suspend
.BI "(struct snd_soc_dapm_context *dapm "  ","
.BI "const char *pin "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dapm" 12
DAPM context
.IP "pin" 12
audio signal pin endpoint (or start point)
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Mark the given endpoint or pin as ignoring suspend.  When the
system is disabled a path between two endpoints flagged as ignoring
suspend will not be disabled.  The path must already be enabled via
normal means at suspend time, it will not be turned on if it was not
already enabled.
